  "prompt": "What is the origin of the the word don (mafia)?",
  "response": "The word \"don\" in the context of the mafia originates from the Spanish and Italian titles of respect, \"don\" or \"donno,\" which traditionally referred to a distinguished gentleman, nobleman, or respected elder. In the Sicilian and Italian-American mafia, \"don\" came to be used as a title of respect for the leader or head of a crime family. The term gained widespread popularity through works of fiction like Mario Puzo's \"The Godfather\" and its film adaptation, which depicted mafia bosses being addressed as \"Don\" followed by their first name (e.g., Don Corleone).",
